fi.helsinki.cs.turridevelop.logic
Class Transition

java.lang.Object
  fi.helsinki.cs.turridevelop.logic.Transition

public class Transition
extends Object

State transition that reads any of given input characters from the tape, optionally writes given character, and optionally moves to the left or to the right.

Constructor Detail

Transition

public Transition(State destination,
                  String inchar,
                  Character outchar,
                  int movement)
Constructs Transition.

Parameters:
destination - The destination state.
inchar - String consisting of the possible characters to read in the transition.
outchar - Character to be written after writing, null if the tape should be left as is.
movement - Movement after reading and writing, negative moves left, positive to the right and zero stays.

public int getMovement()
Get the movement of the tape in this transition.

Returns:
